WhitespaceMinimizedString.name: WhitespaceMinimizedString
WhitespaceMinimizedString.description: A string that has all whitespace trimmed off of beginning and end, and all internal whitespace segments reduced to single spaces. Whitespace includes #x9 (tab), #xA (linefeed), and #xD (carriage return).

Provenance.name: Provenance
Provenance.description: A field containing a DataHarmonizer versioning marker. It is issued by DataHarmonizer when validation is applied to a given row of data.

boolean.name: boolean
notes: If you are authoring schemas in LinkML YAML, the type is referenced with the lower case "boolean".

float.description: A real number that conforms to the xsd:float specification
notes: If you are authoring schemas in LinkML YAML, the type is referenced with the lower case "float".

double.name: double
double.description: A real number that conforms to the xsd:double specification
notes: If you are authoring schemas in LinkML YAML, the type is referenced with the lower case "double".

decimal.name: decimal

notes: If you are authoring schemas in LinkML YAML, the type is referenced with the lower case "decimal".

time.name: time

If you are authoring schemas in LinkML YAML, the type is referenced with the lower case "time".

date.name: date

notes: URI is dateTime because OWL reasoners don't work with straight date or time
If you are authoring schemas in LinkML YAML, the type is referenced with the lower case "date".

datetime.name: datetime
datetime.description: The combination of a date and time
notes: If you are authoring schemas in LinkML YAML, the type is referenced with the lower case "datetime".

date_or_datetime.name: date_or_datetime
date_or_datetime.description: Either a date or a datetime
notes: If you are authoring schemas in LinkML YAML, the type is referenced with the lower case "date_or_datetime".

uriorcurie.name: uriorcurie
notes: If you are authoring schemas in LinkML YAML, the type is referenced with the lower case "uriorcurie".

curie.name: curie
notes: If you are authoring schemas in LinkML YAML, the type is referenced with the lower case "curie".
comments: in RDF serializations this MUST be expanded to a URI
in non-RDF serializations MAY be serialized as the compact representation

uri.name: uri

ncname.name: ncname

objectidentifier.name: objectidentifier
objectidentifier.description: A URI or CURIE that represents an object in the model.
notes: If you are authoring schemas in LinkML YAML, the type is referenced with the lower case "objectidentifier".
comments: Used for inheritance and type checking

nodeidentifier.name: nodeidentifier
nodeidentifier.description: A URI, CURIE or BNODE that represents a node in a model.
notes: If you are authoring schemas in LinkML YAML, the type is referenced with the lower case "nodeidentifier".

jsonpointer.name: jsonpointer
jsonpointer.description: A string encoding a JSON Pointer. The value of the string MUST conform to JSON Point syntax and SHOULD dereference to a valid object within the current instance document when encoded in tree form.
notes: If you are authoring schemas in LinkML YAML, the type is referenced with the lower case "jsonpointer".

jsonpath.name: jsonpath
jsonpath.description: A string encoding a JSON Path. The value of the string MUST conform to JSON Point syntax and SHOULD dereference to zero or more valid objects within the current instance document when encoded in tree form.
notes: If you are authoring schemas in LinkML YAML, the type is referenced with the lower case "jsonpath".

sparqlpath.name: sparqlpath
sparqlpath.description: A string encoding a SPARQL Property Path. The value of the string MUST conform to SPARQL syntax and SHOULD dereference to zero or more valid objects within the current instance document when encoded as RDF.
notes: If you are authoring schemas in LinkML YAML, the type is referenced with the lower case "sparqlpath".

specimen collector sample ID.name: specimen collector sample ID
specimen collector sample ID.description: The user-defined name for the sample.
specimen collector sample ID.title: specimen collector sample ID
comments: Store the collector sample ID. If this number is considered identifiable information, provide an alternative ID. Be sure to store the key that maps between the original and alternative IDs for traceability and follow up if necessary. Every collector sample ID from a single submitter must be unique. It can have any format, but we suggest that you make it concise, unique and consistent within your lab.

specimen collector subsample ID.name: specimen collector subsample ID
specimen collector subsample ID.description: The user-defined identifier assigned to a portion of the original sample.
specimen collector subsample ID.title: specimen collector subsample ID
comments: Store the ID for the subsample/aliquot.

pooled sample ID.name: pooled sample ID
pooled sample ID.description: The user-defined identifier assigned to a combined (pooled) set of samples.
pooled sample ID.title: pooled sample ID
comments: If the sample being analyzed is the result of pooling individual samples, rename the pooled sample with a new identifier. Store the pooled sample ID.

metagenome-assembled genome (MAG) ID.name: metagenome-assembled genome (MAG) ID
metagenome-assembled genome (MAG) ID.description: The user-defined identifier assigned to a genome reconstructed from metagenomic data.
metagenome-assembled genome (MAG) ID.title: metagenome-assembled genome (MAG) ID
comments: Store the MAG ID.

specimen collector project ID.name: specimen collector project ID
specimen collector project ID.description: The user-defined project name assigned to a sequencing project.
specimen collector project ID.title: specimen collector project ID
comments: If the sample was collected or analyzed under the umbrella of a specific project, include the name of that project here.

BioProject accession.name: BioProject accession
BioProject accession.description: The INSDC (i.e., ENA, NCBI, or DDBJ) accession number of the BioProject(s) to which the BioSample belongs.
BioProject accession.title: BioProject accession
comments: Store the BioProject accession number. BioProjects are an organizing tool that links together raw sequence data, assemblies, and their associated metadata. Each province will be assigned a different bioproject accession number by the National Microbiology Lab. A valid NCBI BioProject accession has prefix PRJN e.g., PRJNA12345, and is created once at the beginning of a new sequencing project.

BioSample accession.name: BioSample accession
BioSample accession.description: The identifier assigned to a BioSample in INSDC (i.e., ENA, NCBI, or DDBJ) archives.
BioSample accession.title: BioSample accession
comments: Store the accession returned from the BioSample submission. NCBI BioSamples will have the prefix SAMN, ENA have the prefix SAMEA, DDBJ have SAMD

GenBank accession (versioned).name: GenBank accession (versioned)
GenBank accession (versioned).description: The versioned identifier assigned to an assembly or consensus sequence in GenBank archives.
GenBank accession (versioned).title: GenBank accession (versioned)
comments: Store the versioned GenBank accession assigned to the submitted sequence.

SRA accession.name: SRA accession
SRA accession.description: The Sequence Read Archive (SRA) identifier linking raw read data, methodological metadata and quality control metrics submitted to the INSDC.
SRA accession.title: SRA accession
comments: Store the accession assigned to the submitted sequence. NCBI-SRA accessions start with SRR.

GISAID accession.name: GISAID accession
GISAID accession.description: The identifier assigned to a sequence in GISAID (the Global Initiative on Sharing All Influenza Data) archives.
GISAID accession.title: GISAID accession
comments: Store the accession assigned to the submitted sequence. GISAID accessions start with EPI.

GISAID virus name.name: GISAID virus name
GISAID virus name.description: The user-defined GISAID virus name assigned to the sequence.
GISAID virus name.title: GISAID virus name
comments: GISAID virus names should be in the format "hCoV-19/Country/Identifier/year".

ENA accession.name: ENA accession
ENA accession.description: The identifier assigned to a sequence in the European Nucleotide Archive (ENA).
ENA accession.title: ENA accession
comments: Store the accession assigned to the submitted sequence. ENA sequence accessions start with ERR.

DRA accession.name: DRA accession
DRA accession.description: The identifier assigned to a sequence in DNA Data Bank of Japan (DDBJ) sequence read archives.
DRA accession.title: DRA accession
comments: Store the accession assigned to the submitted sequence. DRA accessions start with DRR.

GSA accession.name: GSA accession
GSA accession.description: The identifier assigned to a BioSample in GSA (Genome Sequence Archive) archives.
GSA accession.title: GSA accession
comments: Store the accession assigned to the submitted sequence. GSA accessions start with CRR.

Enterobase accession.name: Enterobase accession
Enterobase accession.description: The identifier assigned to a sequence in Enterobase archives.
Enterobase accession.title: Enterobase accession
comments: Store the barcode assigned to the submitted sequence. Enterobase barcodes start with different 3 letter codes depending on the organism.

sampling site ID.name: sampling site ID
sampling site ID.description: The user-defined identifier assigned to a specific location from which samples are taken.
sampling site ID.title: sampling site ID
comments: Store the ID for the site from which a sample was taken. The "site" is user defined (e.g. it may be a building and its environs, a specific entity within an environment). Please use the same site ID for all samples from a given site, regardless of when these samples were taken. Any important changes in site location, should be represented with a new site ID.

sampling event ID.name: sampling event ID
sampling event ID.description: The user-defined identifier assigned to a specific event during which one or more samples are taken, from one or more sites.
sampling event ID.title: sampling event ID
comments: Store the ID for the event during which a sample or samples were taken. For example, an event could be one person taking samples from multiple sites, or multiple people taking samples from one site.

sample collection data steward name.name: sample collection data steward name
sample collection data steward name.description: The name of the individual responsible for the data governance, (meta)data usage and distribution of the sample.
sample collection data steward name.title: sample collection data steward name
comments: Provide the name of the sample collection data steward.

sample collected by.name: sample collected by
sample collected by.description: The name of the organization with which the sample collector is affiliated.
sample collected by.title: sample collected by
comments: The name of the agency should be written out in full, (with minor exceptions) and be consistent across multiple submissions.

sample collector contact email.name: sample collector contact email
sample collector contact email.description: The email address of the contact responsible for follow-up regarding the sample.
sample collector contact email.title: sample collector contact email
comments: The email address can represent a specific individual or lab e.g. johnnyblogs@lab.ca, or RespLab@lab.ca

geo loc name (country).name: geo loc name (country)
geo loc name (country).description: The country of origin of the sample.
geo loc name (country).title: geo loc name (country)
comments: If known, select a value from the pick list.

geo loc name (state/province/territory).name: geo loc name (state/province/territory)
geo loc name (state/province/territory).description: The state/province/territory of origin of the sample.
geo loc name (state/province/territory).title: geo loc name (state/province/territory)
comments: Provide the state/province/territory name from the GAZ geography ontology. Search for geography terms here: https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols/ontologies/ga

geo loc name (county/region).name: geo loc name (county/region)
geo loc name (county/region).description: The county/region of origin of the sample.
geo loc name (county/region).title: geo loc name (county/region)
comments: Provide the county/region name from the GAZ geography ontology. Search for geography terms here: https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols/ontologies/gaz

geo loc name (city).name: geo loc name (city)
geo loc name (city).description: The city of origin of the sample.
geo loc name (city).title: geo loc name (city)
comments: Provide the city name from the GAZ geography ontology. Search for geography terms here: https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols/ontologies/gaz

geo loc name (site).name: geo loc name (site)
geo loc name (site).description: The name of a specific geographical location e.g. Credit River (rather than river).
geo loc name (site).title: geo loc name (site)
comments: Provide the name of the specific geographical site using a specific noun (a word that names a certain place, thing).

geo loc latitude.name: geo loc latitude
geo loc latitude.description: The latitude coordinates of the geographical location of sample collection.
geo loc latitude.title: geo loc latitude
comments: Provide latitude coordinates if available. Do not use the centre of the city/region/province/state/country or the location of your agency as a proxy, as this implicates a real location and is misleading. Specify as degrees latitude in format "d[d.dddd] N|S".

geo loc longitude.name: geo loc longitude
geo loc longitude.description: The longitude coordinates of the geographical location of sample collection.
geo loc longitude.title: geo loc longitude
comments: Provide longitude coordinates if available. Do not use the centre of the city/region/province/state/country or the location of your agency as a proxy, as this implicates a real location and is misleading. Specify as degrees longitude in format "d[dd.dddd] W|E".

watershed shapefile availability.name: watershed shapefile availability
watershed shapefile availability.description: The availability status of a shapefile descriping the catchment contributing to a watershed.
watershed shapefile availability.title: watershed shapefile availability
comments: Select a value from the picklist to describe whether or not a watershed shapefile would be available upon request.

watershed shapefile filename.name: watershed shapefile filename
watershed shapefile filename.description: The name of the watershed shapefile.
watershed shapefile filename.title: watershed shapefile filename
comments: Provide the shapefile filename corresponding to the watershed from which the sample was taken. If there are multiple files associated with the watershed, provide all names separated by commas.

purpose of sampling.name: purpose of sampling
purpose of sampling.description: The reason that the sample was collected.
purpose of sampling.title: purpose of sampling
comments: The reason a sample was collected may provide information about potential biases in sampling strategy. Provide the purpose of sampling from the picklist in the template. Most likely, the sample was collected for Public health surveillance. The reason why a sample was originally collected may differ from the reason why it was selected for sequencing, which should be indicated in the "purpose of sequencing" field.

scale of sampling.name: scale of sampling
scale of sampling.description: The range of locations or entities sampled expressed in general terms.
scale of sampling.title: scale of sampling
comments: Provide the scale of wastewater sampling by selecting a value from the picklist.

sample received date.name: sample received date
sample received date.description: The date on which the sample was received.
sample received date.title: sample received date
comments: Provide the sample received date in ISO 8601 format, i.e. "YYYY-MM-DD".

sample collection date.name: sample collection date
sample collection date.description: The date on which the sample was collected, or sampling began for a continuous sample.
sample collection date.title: sample collection date
comments: If your sample is a continuous sample please use this field to capture your start date. Sample collection date is critical for surveillance and many types of analyses. Required granularity includes year, month and day. The date should be provided in ISO 8601 standard format "YYYY-MM-DD".

sample collection end date.name: sample collection end date
sample collection end date.description: The date on which sample collection ended for a continuous sample.
sample collection end date.title: sample collection end date
comments: Provide the date that sample collection ended in ISO 8601 format i.e. YYYY-MM-DD

sample processing date.name: sample processing date
sample processing date.description: The date on which the sample was processed.
sample processing date.title: sample processing date
comments: Provide the sample processed date in ISO 8601 format, i.e. "YYYY-MM-DD". The sample may be collected and processed (e.g. filtered, extraction) on the same day, or on different dates.

sample collection start time.name: sample collection start time
sample collection start time.description: The time at which sample collection began.
sample collection start time.title: sample collection start time
comments: Provide this time in ISO 8601 24hr format, in your local time.

sample collection end time.name: sample collection end time
sample collection end time.description: The time at which sample collection ended.
sample collection end time.title: sample collection end time
comments: Provide this time in ISO 8601 24hr format, in your local time.

sample collection time of day.name: sample collection time of day
sample collection time of day.description: The descriptive time of day during which the sample was collected.
sample collection time of day.title: sample collection time of day
comments: If known, select a value from the pick list. The time of sample processing matters especially for grab samples, as fecal concentration in wastewater fluctuates over the course of the day.

any_of.range: sample collection time of day menu

sample collection time duration value.name: sample collection time duration value
sample collection time duration value.description: The amount of time over which the sample was collected.
sample collection time duration value.title: sample collection time duration value
comments: Provide the numerical value of time.

sample collection time duration unit.name: sample collection time duration unit
sample collection time duration unit.description: The units of the time duration measurement of sample collection.
sample collection time duration unit.title: sample collection time duration unit
comments: Provide the units from the pick list.

presampling activity.name: presampling activity
presampling activity.description: The activities or variables upstream of sample collection that may affect the sample.
presampling activity.title: presampling activity
comments: If there was an activity that would affect the sample prior to collection (this is different than sample processing), provide the activities by selecting one or more values from the template pick list. If the information is unknown or cannot be provided, leave blank or provide a null value.

presampling activity details.name: presampling activity details
presampling activity details.description: The details of the activities or variables that affected the sample collected.
presampling activity details.title: presampling activity details
comments: Briefly describe the presampling activities using free text.

examples.value: Agricultural waste from large farm contributes waste to the site sampled.

sample volume measurement value.name: sample volume measurement value
sample volume measurement value.description: The numerical value of the volume measurement of the sample collected.
sample volume measurement value.title: sample volume measurement value
comments: Provide the numerical value of volume.

sample volume measurement unit.name: sample volume measurement unit
sample volume measurement unit.description: The units of the volume measurement of the sample collected.
sample volume measurement unit.title: sample volume measurement unit
comments: Provide the units from the pick list.

sample storage method.name: sample storage method
sample storage method.description: The process used to store the sample.
sample storage method.title: sample storage method
comments: Provide details of how the sample was stored from time of collection until time of processing. If there were issues with the cold chain storage, note those here.

examples.value: The sample was placed in a tube in a cooler bag during transportation (~3 hours) to the lab site. At this point the sample was placed in storage medium and put in a -10C freezer until it was processed and extracted 5 days later.

sample storage medium.name: sample storage medium
sample storage medium.description: The medium in which a sample is stored.
sample storage medium.title: sample storage medium
comments: Provide the name of the transport medium or storage medium used for this sample. If none was used, leave blank or write "None".

sample storage duration value.name: sample storage duration value
sample storage duration value.description: The numerical value of the time measurement during which a sample is in storage.
sample storage duration value.title: sample storage duration value
comments: Provide the numerical value of time.

sample storage duration unit.name: sample storage duration unit
sample storage duration unit.description: The units of a measured sample storage duration.
sample storage duration unit.title: sample storage duration unit
comments: Provide the units from the pick list.

specimen processing.name: specimen processing
specimen processing.description: Any processing applied to the sample during or after receiving the sample.
specimen processing.title: specimen processing
comments: Select processes from the picklist that were applied to this sample.

specimen processing details.name: specimen processing details
specimen processing details.description: The details of the processing applied to the sample during or after receiving the sample.
specimen processing details.title: specimen processing details
comments: Briefly describe the processes applied to the sample.

examples.value: 25 samples were pooled and further prepared as a single sample during library prep.

experimental protocol field.name: experimental protocol field
experimental protocol field.description: The name of the overarching experimental methodology that was used to process the biomaterial.
experimental protocol field.title: experimental protocol field
comments: Provide the name of the methodology used in your study. If available, provide a link to the protocol.

environmental site.name: environmental site
environmental site.description: An environmental location may describe a site in the natural or built environment e.g. contact surface, metal can, hospital, wet market, bat cave.
environmental site.title: environmental site
comments: Provide a descriptor of the environmental site sampled. Use the picklist provided in the template. If not applicable, choose a null value.

environmental material.name: environmental material
environmental material.description: A substance obtained from the natural or man-made environment e.g. soil, water, sewage.
environmental material.title: environmental material
comments: Provide a descriptor of the environmental material sampled. Use the picklist provided in the template. If not applicable, choose a null value.

environmental material properties.name: environmental material properties
environmental material properties.description: The properties, characteristics and qualities of a substance obtained from the natural or man-made environment.
environmental material properties.title: environmental material properties
comments: Provide the environmental material properties by selecting descriptors from the pick list.

wastewater system type.name: wastewater system type
wastewater system type.description: The type or classification of a wastewater system e.g. sanitary sewer, combined sewer, latrine
wastewater system type.title: wastewater system type
comments: Provide the classification of the wastewater system by selecting from the provided pick list.

experimental specimen role type.name: experimental specimen role type
experimental specimen role type.description: The type of role that the sample represents in the experiment.
experimental specimen role type.title: experimental specimen role type
comments: Samples can play different types of roles in experiments. A sample under study in one experiment may act as a control or be a replicate of another sample in another experiment. This field is used to distinguish samples under study from controls, replicates, etc.  If the sample acted as an experimental control or a replicate, select a role type from the picklist. If the sample was not a control, leave blank or select "Not Applicable".

experimental control details.name: experimental control details
experimental control details.description: The details regarding the experimental control contained in the sample.
experimental control details.title: experimental control details
comments: Provide details regarding the nature of the reference strain used as a control, or what is was used to monitor.

examples.value: Human coronavirus 229E (HCoV-229E) spiked in sample as process control

collection device.name: collection device
collection device.description: The instrument or container used to collect the sample e.g. grab sampler.
collection device.title: collection device
comments: Provide a descriptor of the device used for sampling. Use the picklist provided in the template. If not applicable, choose a null value.

collection method.name: collection method
collection method.description: The process used to collect the sample.
collection method.title: collection method
comments: Provide a descriptor of the collection method used for sampling. Use the picklist provided in the template. If not applicable, choose a null value.

nucleic acid extraction method.name: nucleic acid extraction method
nucleic acid extraction method.description: The process used to extract genomic material from a sample.
nucleic acid extraction method.title: nucleic acid extraction method
comments: Briefly describe the extraction method used.

examples.value: Direct wastewater RNA capture and purification via the "Sewage, Salt, Silica and SARS-CoV-2 (4S)" method v4 found at https://www.protocols.io/view/v-4-direct-wastewater-rna-capture-and-purification-36wgq581ygk5/v4

nucleic acid extraction kit.name: nucleic acid extraction kit
nucleic acid extraction kit.description: The kit used to extract genomic material from a sample
nucleic acid extraction kit.title: nucleic acid extraction kit
comments: Provide the name of the genomic extraction kit used.

endogenous control details.name: endogenous control details
endogenous control details.description: The description of the endogenous controls included when extracting a sample.
endogenous control details.title: endogenous control details
comments: Provide the names of endogenous controls that were used as a reference during extraction. If relevant, include titers of these controls, as well as whether any controls were expected but not identified in the sample.

extraction recovery efficiency measureme.name: extraction recovery efficiency measurement value
extraction recovery efficiency measureme.description: The recovery efficiency of an extraction, calculated as the amount of a synthetic or endogenous compound identified in the sample relative to the amount expected.
extraction recovery efficiency measureme.title: extraction recovery efficiency measurement value
comments: Provide value as a percent.

extraction recovery efficiency measureme.name: extraction recovery efficiency measurement method
extraction recovery efficiency measureme.description: The method by which recovery efficiency of an extraction was calculated.
extraction recovery efficiency measureme.title: extraction recovery efficiency measurement method
comments: Provide a brief description of how extraction recovery efficiency was measured or estimated.

microbiological method.name: microbiological method
microbiological method.description: The laboratory method used to grow, prepare, and/or isolate the microbial isolate.
microbiological method.title: microbiological method
comments: Provide the name and version number of the microbiological method. The ID of the method is also acceptable if the ID can be linked to the laboratory that created the procedure.

strain.name: strain
strain.title: strain
comments: If the isolate represents or is derived from, a lab reference strain or strain from a type culture collection, provide the strain identifier.

isolate ID.name: isolate ID
isolate ID.description: The user-defined identifier for the isolate, as provided by the laboratory that originally isolated the isolate.
isolate ID.title: isolate ID
comments: Provide the isolate_ID created by the lab that first isolated the isolate (i.e. the original isolate ID). If the information is unknown or cannot be provided, leave blank or provide a null value. If only an alternate isolate ID is known (e.g. the ID from your lab, if your lab did not isolate the isolate from the original sample), make asure to include it in the alternative_isolate_ID field.

alternative isolate ID.name: alternative isolate ID
alternative isolate ID.description: An alternative isolate_ID assigned to the isolate by another organization.
alternative isolate ID.title: alternative isolate ID
comments: Alternative isolate IDs should be provided in the in a prescribed format which consists of the ID followed by square brackets (no space in between the ID and bracket) containing the short form of ID providers agency name i.e. ID[short organization code]. An example of a properly formatted alternative_isolate_identifier would be e.g. XYZ4567[CFIA]. Multiple alternative isolate IDs can be provided, separated by semi-colons.

progeny isolate ID.name: progeny isolate ID
progeny isolate ID.description: The identifier assigned to a progenitor isolate derived from an isolate that was directly obtained from a sample.
progeny isolate ID.title: progeny isolate ID
comments: If your sequence data pertains to progeny of an original isolate, provide the progeny_isolate_ID.

isolated by.name: isolated by
isolated by.description: The name of the agency, organization or institution with which the individual who performed the isolation procedure is affiliated.
isolated by.title: isolated by
comments: Provide the name of the agency, organization or institution that isolated the original isolate in full (avoid abbreviations). If the information is unknown or cannot be provided, leave blank or provide a null value.

isolated by laboratory name.name: isolated by laboratory name
isolated by laboratory name.description: The specific laboratory affiliation of the individual who performed the isolation procedure.
isolated by laboratory name.title: isolated by laboratory name
comments: Provide the name of the specific laboratory that that isolated the original isolate (avoid abbreviations). If the information is unknown or cannot be provided, leave blank or provide a null value.

isolated by contact name.name: isolated by contact name
isolated by contact name.description: The name or title of the contact responsible for follow-up regarding the isolate.
